<TITLE> Kabirul Bharasha arrested over brother's killing </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 20 (bdnews24.com)Police arrested on Wednesday former Jatiya Party MP Karim Uddin Bharasa's elder son Kabirul Islam Bharasha on charges of killing his younger son. He was detained at a drug rehabilitation centre in the capital's Uttarkhan area, 23 days into the killing. Paltan police chief Md Majibar Rahman told the reporters on information, they raided Hope of Life at Uttarkhan where he was admitted in the name of Helal Kabirul told the reporters that he had killed his brother Khairul Islam Bharasha for not giving him money as he was to pay Tk 75 lakh to a Bogra cold storage owner. He also told reporters that he had taken Yaba drugs just before the killing. On his confession, the police recovered the pistol used for shooting from his car. Mahmud Hossain, brother of the plaintiff of the case, Imran Hossain, both brothers-in-law of Khairul, told the reporters that Karim and his family were not cooperating as they were trying to save the 'killer'. On Apr 27, Kabirul shot Khairul dead at the latter's Bijojnagar office. That day Rahim Uddin Bharasha told bdnews24.com, "Kabir killed his younger brother Khairul over business feud." bd
